	    "Since I don't smoke, I decided to grow a mustache - it is better for the health.
However, I always carried a jewel-studded cigarette case in which, instead of tobacco, were carefully placed several mustaches, Adolphe Menjou style. I offered them politely to my friends: &quot;Mustache? Mustache? Mustache?&quot;
Nobody dared to touch them. This was my test regarding the sacred aspect of mustaches." -- Salvador Dalí
